<h2>Ordering conditions of SKS Michael Russ GmbH</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Depending on the selected shipping method, a shipping fee is charged per order in addition to the total ticket price. Payment is made by direct debit or credit card.</li>
  <li>The personal data collected during the order process is used exclusively to process the order. The email address is required for the order confirmation.</li>
  <li>Tickets are shipped by post by SKS Michael Russ GmbH at the customer's expense. Unless the purchase is a consumer goods purchase within the meaning of Section 474 of the German Civil Code, shipping is at the customer's risk.</li>
  <li>Tickets remain the property of the respective promoter until final payment has been made.</li>
  <li>If ordered tickets have not arrived within 14 days of the order, the customer must contact SKS Michael Russ GmbH without delay.</li>
  <li>The customer must check the tickets immediately upon receipt for the correct number, price, category, date, time, event and venue.</li>
  <li>Complaints about incorrectly delivered tickets are only possible within two working days of receipt, in writing or by email to SKS Michael Russ GmbH and with return of the incorrectly delivered tickets. The postmark or the date of the email is decisive.</li>
  <li>Special conditions of the respective promoter may apply to individual events. These are announced in the event information and are accepted when purchasing a ticket.</li>
</ol>

<h2>General Terms and Conditions of SKS Michael Russ GmbH</h2>

<p><strong>By purchasing a ticket, the buyer or ticket holder agrees to the following contractual terms of the promoter.</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>The sale of tickets for leisure events that take place at a specific time or within a precisely specified period is not a distance contract within the meaning of Section 312b of the German Civil Code. There is therefore no right of withdrawal or return.</li>
  <li>The promoter has no influence over the design, length, content or volume of the event. Due to their volume, concerts may involve a risk of hearing damage and other health risks.</li>
  <li>Children and young people are subject to child and youth protection rules. Children generally require hearing protection. For concerts with high noise levels, attendance by children under 8 is not recommended. Children up to and including 5 years of age are generally not admitted. Children always require a paid ticket. For safety reasons, strollers, buggies and infant carriers may not be brought along unless this has been expressly communicated otherwise for children's events.</li>
  <li>Claims for damages arising from positive breach of contract, culpa in contrahendo and tort are excluded unless the promoter, its legal representatives or vicarious agents acted intentionally or with gross negligence. In the case of claims due to impossibility of performance or delay, liability for slight negligence is limited to foreseeable damage.</li>
  <li>Glass containers, cans, plastic bottles, pyrotechnic items, umbrellas, drugs, torches, weapons and comparable dangerous or disruptive items may not be brought onto the event site. Deodorants, perfume and similar items are also not permitted on the event site. Violations may result in removal from the premises. Instructions from security staff must be followed; security staff may carry out bag and body checks.</li>
  <li>Only specially marked paths, areas and rooms may be entered on the event site. Barriers and fences may not be moved, climbed over or passed through.</li>
  <li>Tape recorders, film cameras and video cameras may not be brought to the event. Recording functions on mobile phones and smartphones may not be used. Audio, photo, film and video recordings, including for private use, are generally prohibited. Misuse will be prosecuted.</li>
  <li>The promoter reserves the right to refuse admission for good cause. In this case, the face value of the ticket will be refunded.</li>
  <li>When leaving the event site, the ticket loses its validity. Tickets are only taken back if the event is cancelled. Shipping fees are not refunded.</li>
  <li>The promoter may relocate or reschedule the event. A claim for reimbursement of the ticket price due to relocation or rescheduling exists only until the day of the event.</li>
  <li>The support programme may be changed without prior notice.</li>
  <li>The promoter assumes no responsibility for lost or stolen items.</li>
  <li>Resale of tickets is prohibited. Commercial resale and commercial raffles or auctions of tickets are expressly prohibited and will be prosecuted. In private resale, the officially paid admission price may not be exceeded. Otherwise the ticket becomes invalid. Please buy tickets only from known advance booking offices and not from third-party providers.</li>
  <li>The law of the Federal Republic of Germany applies. The place of performance for delivery, services and payment is Stuttgart. If any provision of these terms is invalid, the validity of the remaining provisions remains unaffected.</li>
</ol>

<h2>General information</h2>

<p>Accommodation in and around Stuttgart is available through Stuttgart-Marketing GmbH at www.stuttgart-tourist.de or by phone at +49 (0) 711 22 28 0.</p>
<p>Sleeping in camper vans on public parking spaces in Stuttgart is not permitted. If required, please book a space at www.campingplatz-stuttgart.de in good time.</p>
<p>Please drink enough water at concerts. Even a 90-minute rock concert in the front row without sufficient fluids can be hazardous to your health. Our catering offers food and drinks; drinking water is available in the sanitary areas.</p>
<p>Guests who require a wheelchair space can only be admitted with a ticket specifically issued for that purpose.</p>
<p>If you have problems, complaints or questions, please contact the promoter, box office, security staff or venue management directly on site. Complaints made afterwards are often difficult to resolve. We want you to have the best possible concert experience.</p>
